I would avoid WD-40 like the plague.  WD-40 is not really designed to be
a lubricant despite what the can sez.  Companies like IBM and Xerox no
longer use it in their machines as it has a tendency to dry out and
gum up with time and heat.  I would use a synthetic or silicone based
lubricant created for such applications.

